    "long_instructions": "#### Assessment\r\n\r\nCreate a song with a \"build\" effect, where new tracks are introduced as the song progresses. The song should start with the  Intro Vocal tracks, and then at least 3 new tracks are layered on top. Look at the timeline below to see an example of what this looks like, or listen to the example to hear what this could sound like!\r\n![](https://images.code.org/870f2e6a5519fc27a282dc4c0d8758f2-image-1744149631195.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nThis is an **Assessment** level, which means it covers the key parts of this lesson. Here is a **rubric** describing how this level will be judged - click each of the rows below to expand the rubric.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<details open>\r\n  <summary><strong>Extensive Evidence</strong></summary>\r\n  The song contains at least 4 different tracks that are layered together to create a complex song that \"builds\". New tracks are introduced at different start times and all tracks end at the same time.\r\n</details>\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary><strong>Convincing Evidence</strong></summary>\r\n  The song contains at least 4 different tracks that start and stop at different times, but the song does not create a \"build\" effect based on how the tracks are sequenced.\r\n</details>\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary><strong>Limited Evidence</strong></summary>\r\n  The song contains at least 4 tracks but several of them start at the same time\r\n</details>\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary><strong>No Evidence</strong></summary>\r\n  The song does not have enough tracks or all of them start at the same time.\r\n</details>",
